My Money App Front-End Documentation

Overview

My Money is an expense tracker app designed to help users manage their finances effectively. The app features a user-friendly interface and is built using React Native, CSS, and JavaScript.

Features

•⁠  ⁠Expense tracking: Users can add and categorize their expenses with ease.
•⁠  ⁠Budgeting: Users can set a budget and receive alerts when they go over budget.
•⁠  ⁠Financial goals: Users can set and track financial goals, such as saving for a specific purpose.
•⁠  ⁠Dashboard overview: A graph showing expense categories, a list of recent transactions, a budget tracker, and a financial goals progress bar.
•⁠  ⁠About Us page: Information about the app and its developers.

Front-End Tools

•⁠  ⁠React Native: Used for building the app's UI components and structure.
•⁠  ⁠CSS: Used for styling and layout.
•⁠  ⁠JavaScript: Used for dynamic functionality and interactions.
. html

Dashboard

•⁠  ⁠Graph: Displays expense categories and their respective percentages.
•⁠  ⁠Recent transactions: Lists the user's most recent transactions.
•⁠  ⁠Budget tracker: Displays the user's budget and alerts them when they go over budget.
•⁠  ⁠Financial goals: Displays the user's financial goals and their progress.

